<item>
            <title>[PIG-2019] smoketest-jar target has to depend on pigunit-jar to guarantee inclusion of test classes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2019</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;pigsmoke artifact uses classes from pigunit for real cluster testing. However, in the deployment phase the artifact comes out without the classes added. It happens because of the execution order of targets during deployment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12505422">PIG-2019</key>
            <summary>smoketest-jar target has to depend on pigunit-jar to guarantee inclusion of test classes</summary>
